<BLOCKQUOTE>Posted by
Puggles of Bertoxxulous on 17:10:10 9/1/1999 from 24.4.252.247:<p>
In reply to: <a href="http://cor.simplenet.com/Mage/mageboard.mv?parm_func=showmsg+parm_msgnum=1000153">High Lvl Ward Summoned Spells</a> posted by 
Azzlan on 13:27:22 8/31/1999 from 204.116.231.87:<p>
All ward spells, be it Ward Summoned, Ward Undead, or the like, have their uses. Ward->Expulse->Dismiss->etc. line of Undead spells are useful bar far in Lower Guk, killing Spectres, and literally tons of other beasties. The summoned class does not seem as useful, and honestly it is not, but it's an asset that Magicians get, and should be taken seriously just like all our other spells. (If you can't tell by now, I for one think Magicians are very powerful if you look at the Big Picture and play them right.) <br><br>Our Ward Summons are useful in the following places that I can remember off the top of my head:<br>Lavastorm<br>Najena<br>Lower Guk<br>Soluesk A<br>Soluesk B (Nagafen)<br>Unrest<br>Mistmoore<br>Mountians of Rathe<br>West Karana<br>Beholder Maze<br><br>and everywhere else you fight spellcasting NPCs.<br><br>Why?<br><br>Think about what all are SUMMONED... Elementals, Skeletons, Wolves (Shaman pets), the Enchanter sword/shield whatchamacallits and everything of that nature.<br><br>I'll give a quick example that the ward summons saved my group. =)<br><br>Our group decided to travel to Rathe Mountians and kill the good Sphinx there. The Sphinx is a level 40 enchanter. Meaning he has a pet. Attack started. Sphinx charmed a caster. Bad news - but this was thought of. My job was clear. Make pet. Buff pet (burnout). Send pet in to attack Sphinx. Nullify Magic anyone who gets charmed. If I get charmed, than one of our necros nullifies me.<br><br>I nullified the guy who was charmed. Good deal. He rejoins the fight. It goes well till the pet goes nuts on one of our necromancers. We had no choice but to continue beatin on the the sphinx. So, since my part was to assist, (even though I have good DD), I sat down real fast, and memorized Dismiss Summoned. The pet was mine =) Considering it killed one of our necromancers already, I feel that I did tip the battle =) We did win, and the pet died pretty fast after I started beating it up.<br><br>Anyway. That concludes my spiel on our Wards.<br><br>Magicians are THE masters of everything summoned. 'Nuff said. =)<br><br>Puggles Snuggles<br>36 Magician<br>Bertoxxulous
</MvEVAL>
</BLOCKQUOTE><hr width=90%><p>
